When you compile this document, LaTeX will generate a TOC at the location of the `\tableofcontents` command, listing all the sections and subsections in your document.

If you want to customize the appearance of the TOC, you can use various options with the `toc` package. For example, you can change the font size, spacing, and formatting of the TOC entries. Here's an example:

